WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

2
00:00:03.420 --> 00:00:07.240
Try to always get along with Taku-chan.

3
00:00:09.860 --> 00:00:11.870
You take good care of him.

4
00:00:11.870 --> 00:00:14.920
U-Um, ma'am! It's not like that!

5
00:00:14.920 --> 00:00:16.420
It's not like...

6
00:00:18.460 --> 00:00:19.860
Hon?

7
00:00:21.760 --> 00:00:25.250
Oh no, heatstroke! Someone help!

8
00:00:27.260 --> 00:00:28.580
H-Honjoji-san!

9
00:00:28.580 --> 00:00:30.010
I'll ring Dr. Whiskers.

10
00:00:30.010 --> 00:00:31.880
You get her inside.

11
00:00:31.880 --> 00:00:33.040
A-All right.

12
00:00:33.370 --> 00:00:35.330
You're gonna be okay!

13
00:00:36.560 --> 00:00:38.350
<i>Sh-She's heavy!</i>

14
00:00:38.350 --> 00:00:39.920
<i>My back's gonna break!</i>

15
00:00:46.600 --> 00:00:47.730
Dad?!

16
00:02:19.490 --> 00:02:23.410
How about We Travel Together?

17
00:02:20.380 --> 00:02:22.610
T-Takuya!

18
00:02:27.540 --> 00:02:29.780
What are you doin' here?!

19
00:02:29.780 --> 00:02:31.670
Never mind, we need to lay her down!

20
00:02:31.670 --> 00:02:33.390
Be gentle about it!

21
00:02:33.390 --> 00:02:34.990
Gentle...

22
00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:37.270
Everyone's waitin' for you at home!

23
00:02:37.270 --> 00:02:39.050
I was going to contact you.

24
00:02:39.310 --> 00:02:43.180
This lady... Didn't I meet her 
the other day in Tokyo?

25
00:02:43.590 --> 00:02:46.280
<i>What happened to me?</i>

26
00:02:46.280 --> 00:02:48.440
<i>Someone's touching me.</i>

27
00:02:48.850 --> 00:02:51.630
<i>Don't, I'm all sweaty.</i>

28
00:02:51.940 --> 00:02:55.410
What's going on? What's she doing here?

29
00:02:55.410 --> 00:02:58.450
I heard you were comin' 
on account of the wedding!

30
00:02:58.450 --> 00:03:00.200
Hold on, is she...

31
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:01.950
U-Uh...

32
00:03:01.950 --> 00:03:03.810
Aww, it hurts.

33
00:03:02.470 --> 00:03:04.470
Did you call your Aunt Kyoko?

34
00:03:04.470 --> 00:03:08.490
I know you haven't seen her lately, but 
she looked after you when you were young!

35
00:03:08.490 --> 00:03:09.880
Dad, listen!

36
00:03:10.710 --> 00:03:12.920
I ain't gettin' married!

37
00:03:14.170 --> 00:03:16.100
Aww, it hurts.

38
00:03:16.100 --> 00:03:17.180
Huh?!

39
00:03:17.180 --> 00:03:21.060
I know I caused problems 
by not fessin' up until now.

40
00:03:21.060 --> 00:03:22.600
I'm really sorry.

41
00:03:24.240 --> 00:03:26.600
This is gonna take more than a "sorry."

42
00:03:28.230 --> 00:03:30.510
You got any idea how much—

43
00:03:30.510 --> 00:03:33.110
Grandpa's sleepin' in there! 
Bring her in here!

44
00:03:33.110 --> 00:03:36.140
Any idea how much I've been 
runnin' around over this?!

45
00:03:36.140 --> 00:03:38.030
Th-That's why I apologized!

46
00:03:38.030 --> 00:03:40.720
You coulda told me it was a lie in Tokyo!

47
00:03:40.720 --> 00:03:43.500
Oh, Takuya. Keep her head supported.

48
00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:45.380
Oh, g-got it.

49
00:03:45.380 --> 00:03:48.000
You've always taken too long to do stuff.

50
00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:50.130
It was the same story with swimming!

51
00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:53.210
Swimming?! That was back in grade school!

52
00:03:53.210 --> 00:03:54.640
And with curry!

53
00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:55.510
Curry?!

54
00:03:55.510 --> 00:03:58.710
When you eat curry, 
there's always rice left over.

55
00:03:58.710 --> 00:04:00.490
You never plan ahead!

56
00:04:00.490 --> 00:04:02.050
How's that even related?

57
00:04:02.050 --> 00:04:05.130
You add too much sauce! It ain't unlimited!

58
00:04:05.130 --> 00:04:06.700
Quit goin' on about the sauce!

59
00:04:06.700 --> 00:04:08.480
I put out a futon!

60
00:04:13.340 --> 00:04:15.480
It ain't heatstroke.

61
00:04:15.780 --> 00:04:17.900
If anything, she's tuckered out.

62
00:04:17.900 --> 00:04:20.400
Just let her get some rest.

63
00:04:25.620 --> 00:04:28.520
Thank you so much, Doctor.

64
00:04:29.540 --> 00:04:31.570
I'll apologize to everyone at home.

65
00:04:31.570 --> 00:04:32.790
If you say so.

66
00:04:35.270 --> 00:04:36.410
Takuya.

67
00:04:37.500 --> 00:04:41.010
It's high time you stopped 
livin' life so half-assed.

68
00:04:41.010 --> 00:04:42.580
Don't let me down!

69
00:04:45.650 --> 00:04:48.310
<i>I don't live my life half-assed.</i>

70
00:04:48.310 --> 00:04:50.350
It's all my fault!

71
00:04:50.350 --> 00:04:53.470
'Cause I had her snippin' melons! Sorry!

72
00:04:54.470 --> 00:04:56.020
It ain't your fault, Grandma!

73
00:04:56.020 --> 00:04:57.740
That's right, don't you fret!

74
00:04:58.110 --> 00:05:00.110
I really am sorry.

75
00:05:00.110 --> 00:05:02.740
Like the doctor said, she's all right.

76
00:05:06.720 --> 00:05:07.750
Huh?!

77
00:05:07.750 --> 00:05:09.400
You're not gettin' hitched?!

78
00:05:09.400 --> 00:05:12.620
You're kiddin'! I bought 
a present and everything!

79
00:05:13.110 --> 00:05:15.900
I know I caused trouble for you two and Mom.

80
00:05:16.370 --> 00:05:17.200
I'm sorry.

81
00:05:17.200 --> 00:05:18.630
It's Taku-chan!

82
00:05:18.630 --> 00:05:21.570
We jumped to the wrong conclusion?

83
00:05:21.570 --> 00:05:25.050
But a fake marriage, though. 
It's like a TV show.

84
00:05:25.050 --> 00:05:28.140
Guess I cooked too much food, then.

85
00:05:28.140 --> 00:05:31.020
Fess up, how in tarnation 
did all this happen?

86
00:05:31.020 --> 00:05:32.980
Yeah, yeah. Tell us.

87
00:05:32.980 --> 00:05:35.620
What's this coworker of yours like?

88
00:05:35.620 --> 00:05:37.840
Should we go check up on her?

89
00:05:37.840 --> 00:05:40.650
N-No, don't worry about it.

90
00:05:40.650 --> 00:05:42.590
Taku-chan, how long'll you be here?

91
00:05:42.590 --> 00:05:44.030
Taku-chan, let's play!

92
00:05:44.030 --> 00:05:46.530
Taku-chan! Taku-chan!

93
00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:47.760
Let's play!

94
00:05:48.310 --> 00:05:50.940
Sorry, they're always so noisy.

95
00:05:51.300 --> 00:05:53.540
I'm just glad they were in a good mood.

96
00:05:53.540 --> 00:05:56.040
Say hello to your grandma for me.

97
00:05:56.040 --> 00:05:56.970
Will do.

98
00:05:56.970 --> 00:06:01.960
Your dad'll probably be mad for a while, 
but I'll get him to simmer down.

99
00:06:02.270 --> 00:06:03.430
Sorry.

100
00:06:03.430 --> 00:06:05.200
Never you mind.

101
00:06:06.170 --> 00:06:10.000
That young lady's important 
to you now, ain't she?

102
00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:12.040
You'd best look out for her.

103
00:06:12.400 --> 00:06:14.330
Yeah, I know.

104
00:06:16.820 --> 00:06:18.200
Hang in there!

105
00:06:25.430 --> 00:06:27.660
Welcome back, Taku-chan.

106
00:06:28.020 --> 00:06:29.530
You done talkin' to 'em?

107
00:06:29.530 --> 00:06:31.900
Yeah. How's Honjoji-san?

108
00:06:31.900 --> 00:06:34.290
Still asleep, looks like.

109
00:06:34.290 --> 00:06:36.410
She sure was tired.

110
00:06:36.410 --> 00:06:38.670
<i>I'll leave her be until she feels better.</i>

111
00:06:38.670 --> 00:06:40.630
<i>We can leave anytime.</i>

112
00:06:40.930 --> 00:06:43.260
I'm gonna turn in for the night.

113
00:06:43.260 --> 00:06:45.980
Me too. Today was exhausting.

114
00:06:46.390 --> 00:06:49.140
I put out a futon upstairs.

115
00:06:49.140 --> 00:06:51.270
Thank you. Good night.

116
00:06:52.750 --> 00:06:55.790
<i>I can still feel Honjoji-san's warmth.</i>

117
00:07:04.900 --> 00:07:07.870
<i>I'm in the same room as her?!</i>

118
00:07:07.870 --> 00:07:10.120
<i>Why, Grandma?!</i>

119
00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:12.950
<i>I-I need to move this futon somewhere else.</i>

120
00:07:13.360 --> 00:07:15.760
<i>No way am I sleeping here!</i>

121
00:07:20.420 --> 00:07:23.920
<i>Huh? What happened to me?!</i>

122
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:25.270
Ohara-kun?!

123
00:07:27.600 --> 00:07:30.330
Uh, look! This futon isn't what you think!

124
00:07:30.330 --> 00:07:33.970
H-Have I been asleep this whole time?

125
00:07:33.970 --> 00:07:36.500
Yes, you collapsed 
in the yard this afternoon.

126
00:07:36.500 --> 00:07:37.140
What?!

127
00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:38.840
Are you all right?

128
00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:40.650
Yes, I'm much better now.

129
00:07:44.510 --> 00:07:48.410
Uh, what happened with you going back home?

130
00:07:48.410 --> 00:07:50.180
Oh, that.

131
00:07:50.180 --> 00:07:52.570
I already went and apologized to everyone.

132
00:07:52.570 --> 00:07:53.360
Huh?

133
00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:54.830
So, everything is fine now.

134
00:07:54.830 --> 00:07:57.570
No, I'll apologize to them too!

135
00:07:57.570 --> 00:08:00.210
No, you can just take it easy.

136
00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:04.000
<i>The only thing I accomplished 
was taking a nap.</i>

137
00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:05.740
<i>Talk about awkward.</i>

138
00:08:06.050 --> 00:08:08.280
<i>Tomorrow, I'll go apologize properly.</i>

139
00:08:13.650 --> 00:08:15.930
That sounds like a lot of frogs.

140
00:08:15.930 --> 00:08:17.880
That's a country night for you.

141
00:08:19.020 --> 00:08:22.860
Um, is it okay if we go outside for a while?

142
00:08:22.860 --> 00:08:24.560
Oh, sure.

143
00:08:27.770 --> 00:08:29.100
It's so dark.

144
00:08:29.100 --> 00:08:30.740
That's a country night for you.

145
00:08:31.110 --> 00:08:33.200
It gets very bright when the moon is out.

146
00:08:46.110 --> 00:08:48.610
A-Are you okay?

147
00:08:49.470 --> 00:08:51.140
I-I'm fine!

148
00:08:54.820 --> 00:08:56.190
It's a tree frog.

149
00:08:56.190 --> 00:08:58.310
<i>He's good at catching them.</i>

150
00:09:10.450 --> 00:09:16.210
Tell me, were you the one 
who carried me this afternoon?

151
00:09:16.700 --> 00:09:19.380
Yes, my father and I did.

152
00:09:19.380 --> 00:09:21.460
I'm sorry for the inconvenience.

153
00:09:22.590 --> 00:09:25.090
I was immersed in what I was doing.

154
00:09:25.640 --> 00:09:29.220
I got so into cutting melons, 
I lost track of everything.

155
00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:31.590
That must have been why I collapsed.

156
00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:37.310
Maybe I enjoyed it more than I realized.

157
00:09:37.730 --> 00:09:42.310
Meeting you has taken me 
to some curious places.

158
00:09:43.030 --> 00:09:47.690
I've been on plenty of trips, 
but never one like this.

159
00:09:49.220 --> 00:09:52.730
Although I probably shouldn't 
be having such thoughts.

160
00:09:52.730 --> 00:09:54.170
U-Um...

161
00:09:54.570 --> 00:09:58.890
You gave me that stone before, 
the frog-shaped stone.

162
00:09:59.240 --> 00:10:02.120
I placed it in front of my TV.

163
00:10:02.120 --> 00:10:06.800
I'd never been given that sort of thing, 
so it made me... happy.

164
00:10:07.490 --> 00:10:13.070
When I look at the stone it... 
always makes me think of you.

165
00:10:23.590 --> 00:10:25.760
<i>This peculiar experience.</i>

166
00:10:26.650 --> 00:10:28.940
<i>A trip only two people can take.</i>

167
00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:30.740
<i>Maybe...</i>

168
00:10:31.090 --> 00:10:35.080
<i>Maybe this is... marriage.</i>

169
00:10:36.400 --> 00:10:38.870
Uh, that's why I'm...

170
00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:41.330
I'm glad you—

171
00:10:41.870 --> 00:10:43.580
Ribbit

172
00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:49.090
Ribbit

173
00:10:43.620 --> 00:10:49.090
Croak

174
00:10:44.760 --> 00:10:47.320
So many frogs croaking.

175
00:10:47.320 --> 00:10:49.090
It is the countryside, and all.

176
00:10:49.090 --> 00:10:51.520
L-Let's head on back.

177
00:10:51.520 --> 00:10:53.350
Y-Yes, let's.

178
00:10:53.770 --> 00:10:56.220
Oh, I'll... move my futon out of that room.

179
00:10:56.220 --> 00:10:59.050
R-Right. Thank you.

180
00:10:59.970 --> 00:11:04.980
Croak

181
00:11:15.560 --> 00:11:17.320
<i>I didn't sleep well.</i>

182
00:11:17.630 --> 00:11:19.910
Uh, that's why I'm...

183
00:11:20.170 --> 00:11:21.850
I'm glad you—

184
00:11:22.740 --> 00:11:26.600
<i>What was Ohara-kun going to say after that?</i>

185
00:11:26.600 --> 00:11:27.780
<i>I wish I knew.</i>

186
00:11:29.700 --> 00:11:30.890
<i>No, no, no.</i>

187
00:11:30.890 --> 00:11:32.670
<i>You're overthinking this!</i>

188
00:11:32.980 --> 00:11:35.950
<i>It's not a big deal anyway, no.</i>

189
00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:39.340
Good morning, hon.

190
00:11:39.340 --> 00:11:41.290
Oh, good morning.

191
00:11:41.290 --> 00:11:43.550
Breakfast is ready.

192
00:11:47.130 --> 00:11:48.980
Good morning.

193
00:11:49.390 --> 00:11:50.430
Ohara-kun?

194
00:11:50.430 --> 00:11:52.090
G-Good morning.

195
00:11:52.090 --> 00:11:54.980
Uh, sorry for all the mess yesterday.

196
00:11:54.980 --> 00:11:56.150
I'm sorry too.

197
00:11:56.420 --> 00:11:58.660
How are you feeling?

198
00:12:01.760 --> 00:12:03.290
I-I'm fine.

199
00:12:03.560 --> 00:12:04.220
Uh...

200
00:12:04.220 --> 00:12:06.080
I really am fine!

201
00:12:06.080 --> 00:12:08.630
I-I'm just not quite done getting ready.

202
00:12:08.630 --> 00:12:10.330
Oh, I'm sorry!

203
00:12:15.010 --> 00:12:16.920
Leavin' so soon?

204
00:12:16.920 --> 00:12:20.320
Sorry you had such a rough spell.

205
00:12:20.320 --> 00:12:21.680
No, it's okay.

206
00:12:21.680 --> 00:12:25.640
I'll send you some melons. 
Y'all come back now, hear?

207
00:12:25.640 --> 00:12:27.430
I appreciate your kindness.

208
00:12:29.090 --> 00:12:31.440
We're really going to my parents' place?

209
00:12:31.440 --> 00:12:34.190
Yes, I'm going to apologize too.

210
00:12:34.510 --> 00:12:37.180
It takes about 20 minutes to walk there.

211
00:12:37.180 --> 00:12:38.790
I don't mind at all.

212
00:12:38.790 --> 00:12:41.370
All right, then.

213
00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:49.120
<i>He has bedhead. His hair is all fluffy.</i>

214
00:12:49.120 --> 00:12:52.120
<i>Looks like it'd feel nice 
to run my hands through it.</i>

215
00:12:53.880 --> 00:12:58.200
<i>Cut that out. I didn't come here 
to think about things like that!</i>

216
00:12:58.840 --> 00:13:00.790
Um, Honjoji-san.

217
00:13:01.400 --> 00:13:02.880
It's this way.

218
00:13:05.540 --> 00:13:06.850
Huh?!

219
00:13:06.850 --> 00:13:08.490
Honjoji-san...

220
00:13:08.490 --> 00:13:09.780
...from JTC!

221
00:13:09.780 --> 00:13:11.810
You made a special trip here?

222
00:13:12.160 --> 00:13:15.190
I'm truly sorry for all the fuss I caused.

223
00:13:15.190 --> 00:13:17.220
Oh, not at all.

224
00:13:17.220 --> 00:13:20.090
Looks like it's my son 
who caused you the fuss.

225
00:13:20.090 --> 00:13:21.270
N-No!

226
00:13:21.270 --> 00:13:24.620
I heard 'bout that horrible job transfer.

227
00:13:24.620 --> 00:13:26.720
Where was it? Aizuwakamatsu?

228
00:13:26.720 --> 00:13:27.930
Anchorage.

229
00:13:27.930 --> 00:13:29.830
It's a hell of a plan.

230
00:13:29.830 --> 00:13:30.620
Sure is.

231
00:13:30.620 --> 00:13:32.370
That's Tokyo for ya.

232
00:13:32.370 --> 00:13:35.180
Where would you <i>like</i> to go overseas?

233
00:13:32.790 --> 00:13:34.240
<i>Can she handle them?</i>

234
00:13:34.240 --> 00:13:36.500
Taku-chan, why're you just standin' there?

235
00:13:35.180 --> 00:13:37.800
I could go for an overseas job transfer.

236
00:13:36.500 --> 00:13:38.620
Huh? Oh, well...

237
00:13:38.620 --> 00:13:42.460
You came all this way. 
Why not show her around Aso?

238
00:13:42.460 --> 00:13:45.010
Doesn't your return flight leave tonight?

239
00:13:45.010 --> 00:13:49.380
Oh, but I haven't gotten 
to apologize to his father.

240
00:13:49.380 --> 00:13:53.140
Sorry about that. Our father 
went to work again today.

241
00:13:53.140 --> 00:13:56.400
He's too embarrassed, bless his heart.

242
00:13:56.400 --> 00:14:00.100
But what's worth seein' in 
these parts beyond the scenery?

243
00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:01.110
Th—

244
00:14:01.150 --> 00:14:02.990
The volcano museum!

245
00:14:10.280 --> 00:14:12.500
Y'all have fun!

246
00:14:13.190 --> 00:14:17.270
I'm sorry. It ended up 
sounding like I was insisting.

247
00:14:17.270 --> 00:14:20.270
That's okay. I'm glad there was 
somewhere you wanted to go.

248
00:14:20.720 --> 00:14:24.130
I've actually been wanting 
to go for a while now.

249
00:14:24.130 --> 00:14:26.340
The Aso Volcano Museum.

250
00:14:26.340 --> 00:14:29.060
I don't think I've been there 
since a grade-school field trip.

251
00:14:38.790 --> 00:14:42.320
Looks like there isn't much fog today.

252
00:14:42.320 --> 00:14:44.300
It's wonderful!

253
00:14:44.300 --> 00:14:47.240
I can suddenly hear 
the <i>Bochi Komori</i> theme song!

254
00:14:47.240 --> 00:14:48.880
<i>Bochi Komori</i>?

255
00:14:48.880 --> 00:14:51.900
Oh, that show where they walk around towns.

256
00:14:51.900 --> 00:14:53.330
I've watched it plenty myself.

257
00:14:53.330 --> 00:14:54.440
Right.

258
00:14:54.440 --> 00:14:59.380
That soothing melody that makes me want 
to travel is playing right now in my ears!

259
00:14:59.750 --> 00:15:03.760
Honjoji Rika

260
00:14:59.750 --> 00:15:03.760
Komori

261
00:14:59.750 --> 00:15:28.620
Bochi Komori
Aso

262
00:15:00.070 --> 00:15:01.940
This is <i>Bochi Komori</i>.

263
00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:03.760
Today, we're here in Aso.

264
00:15:04.020 --> 00:15:08.670
Thousand-meter tall mountains tower 
over this world-class caldera,

265
00:15:08.670 --> 00:15:11.010
and there seems to be plenty worth seeing.

266
00:15:11.010 --> 00:15:13.700
Let's go ahead and get to it, Komori-san.

267
00:15:13.700 --> 00:15:14.440
You got it.

268
00:15:14.440 --> 00:15:18.350
<i>Mount Aso is an active volcano, with 
smoke rising from it this very moment.</i>

269
00:15:18.350 --> 00:15:21.740
<i>We've been told nobody 
is allowed in on certain days,</i>

270
00:15:21.740 --> 00:15:23.330
<i>but things seem fine today.</i>

271
00:15:23.330 --> 00:15:26.840
<i>So, let's start in on today's 
episode of </i>Bochi Komori<i>.</i>

272
00:15:27.380 --> 00:15:28.620
Honjoji-san?

273
00:15:29.870 --> 00:15:31.770
Uh, Honjoji-san?

274
00:15:31.770 --> 00:15:32.620
Excuse me.

275
00:15:33.260 --> 00:15:34.360
Honjoji-san?

276
00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:37.520
Sorry, please come back!

277
00:15:57.640 --> 00:16:01.650
Formation of the Aso Volcano

278
00:16:25.580 --> 00:16:29.050
This is a good view of both 
Mount Naka and Kusasenri.

279
00:16:29.050 --> 00:16:32.190
The entirety of Kusasenri 
is in the outer caldera.

280
00:16:32.190 --> 00:16:32.890
Huh?

281
00:16:32.890 --> 00:16:35.870
And the pond on the east side 
is in the inner caldera.

282
00:16:35.870 --> 00:16:37.730
It's what they call a double volcano.

283
00:16:37.730 --> 00:16:39.680
D-Double?

284
00:16:40.310 --> 00:16:43.750
The inner caldera was formed 
when a lava dome blew off,

285
00:16:43.750 --> 00:16:46.780
and part of it still remains 
as Komatate-yama Hill.

286
00:16:48.340 --> 00:16:51.790
That's the reason this mountain 
has bilateral asymmetry.

287
00:16:51.790 --> 00:16:55.120
Wow, check out the view!

288
00:16:59.120 --> 00:17:00.770
Hey!

289
00:17:00.770 --> 00:17:03.560
Come on, you're botherin' the other patrons!

290
00:17:03.560 --> 00:17:05.630
I really need you to stop!

291
00:17:07.920 --> 00:17:09.630
I-I'm sorry.

292
00:17:09.630 --> 00:17:10.800
It's okay.

293
00:17:10.800 --> 00:17:13.850
Please, I'm begging you.

294
00:17:17.560 --> 00:17:21.370
Okay! Listen, who here can be quiet?

295
00:17:22.310 --> 00:17:26.130
Hey, good for you. 
You did a great job being quiet.

296
00:17:26.130 --> 00:17:27.530
Way to go.

297
00:17:28.210 --> 00:17:29.530
Ohara-kun?

298
00:17:29.910 --> 00:17:32.180
I thought back to our rookie training.

299
00:17:32.180 --> 00:17:34.780
It's a trick for leading grade-schoolers.

300
00:17:35.060 --> 00:17:37.290
All children are eager for praise.

301
00:17:37.290 --> 00:17:40.290
So, if you start by praising 
the ones who quiet down,

302
00:17:40.290 --> 00:17:42.800
the rest should follow their lead.

303
00:17:45.990 --> 00:17:49.740
D-Do all of you know about the Kicking Myth?

304
00:17:50.550 --> 00:17:55.170
A god broke Mount Aso 
by giving it a hard kick.

305
00:17:55.170 --> 00:17:56.460
Or so the story goes.

306
00:17:56.460 --> 00:17:58.560
Say what now?

307
00:18:00.040 --> 00:18:01.940
I-It's said that...

308
00:18:01.940 --> 00:18:05.650
i-it happened to the south, 
at Tateno Crater Shallows.

309
00:18:05.650 --> 00:18:07.780
Tateno Crater Shallows?

310
00:18:07.780 --> 00:18:10.620
Have you heard of a placed called Tateno?

311
00:18:10.620 --> 00:18:12.290
Yeah! I have!

312
00:18:12.290 --> 00:18:16.070
It's called that because 
after the god did his kick,

313
00:18:16.070 --> 00:18:18.740
he fell over and said "Taten no." 
("I can't get up.")

314
00:18:19.250 --> 00:18:20.250
You're kiddin'!

315
00:18:20.250 --> 00:18:21.860
That's a dad joke!

316
00:18:22.960 --> 00:18:24.340
Crazy!

317
00:18:42.090 --> 00:18:44.080
Bye bye!

318
00:18:44.080 --> 00:18:46.300
See ya!

319
00:18:54.610 --> 00:18:56.180
Are you tired?

320
00:18:56.180 --> 00:18:58.120
Huh? N-No.

321
00:18:58.440 --> 00:19:01.660
Looks like my sister will take us 
to the airport on her way home,

322
00:19:01.660 --> 00:19:03.580
so this was perfect timing.

323
00:19:03.580 --> 00:19:04.680
Right.

324
00:19:04.680 --> 00:19:08.790
This trip was kind of hectic 
the whole time. Sorry.

325
00:19:08.790 --> 00:19:11.120
No, it's fine!

326
00:19:12.770 --> 00:19:16.370
<i>His hair looks really nice to touch.</i>

327
00:19:18.360 --> 00:19:22.990
<i>Meeting you has taken me 
to some curious places.</i>

328
00:19:24.070 --> 00:19:25.960
<i>This peculiar experience.</i>

329
00:19:26.470 --> 00:19:28.860
<i>A trip only two people can take.</i>

330
00:19:40.740 --> 00:19:43.350
I'll go let my sister know we're here.

331
00:19:43.350 --> 00:19:44.300
All right.

332
00:19:56.070 --> 00:19:57.030
Nao?

333
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.110
Takuya?!

334
00:19:58.110 --> 00:20:00.220
What're <i>you</i> doin' here?!

335
00:20:00.220 --> 00:20:04.300
Right back atcha! 
When did you come back to Aso?!

336
00:20:04.300 --> 00:20:06.730
Oh, Nao-chan. You're here.

337
00:20:06.730 --> 00:20:09.500
Hi there, ma'am!

338
00:20:09.500 --> 00:20:11.560
I finished another new one.

339
00:20:11.830 --> 00:20:14.570
Really? Show us!

340
00:20:15.940 --> 00:20:17.720
It's so purty!

341
00:20:17.720 --> 00:20:20.980
Look, Takuya. Nao-chan made this plate.

342
00:20:20.980 --> 00:20:24.320
You really became a glassmaker?

343
00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:26.830
For three years now. You didn't know?

344
00:20:26.830 --> 00:20:30.640
That's amazin'. You've always 
been good at everything.

345
00:20:30.640 --> 00:20:33.530
R-Really? Thanks.

346
00:20:34.250 --> 00:20:37.270
Nao, I came here with a coworker.

347
00:20:37.270 --> 00:20:39.590
U-Um, hello.

348
00:20:39.590 --> 00:20:43.810
Her name's Nao. We've been 
neighbors since we were born.

349
00:20:44.810 --> 00:20:46.830
I-I-I'm Miyama Nao!

350
00:20:46.830 --> 00:20:49.820
Pardon me for not greeting you sooner!

351
00:20:49.820 --> 00:20:52.230
I'm Honjoji. Nice to meet you.

352
00:20:52.230 --> 00:20:55.060
Did my standard Japanese sound okay?

353
00:20:55.060 --> 00:20:55.780
Huh?

354
00:20:55.780 --> 00:20:58.710
What're you gettin' all respectful for, Nao?

355
00:20:59.560 --> 00:21:02.530
Don't be so condescendin', Takuya!

356
00:21:03.370 --> 00:21:05.730
Bein' in Tokyo makes you mister big shot?!

357
00:21:05.730 --> 00:21:07.700
What are you, a child?!

358
00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:10.440
Your hair's as crazy as ever!

359
00:21:10.440 --> 00:21:12.590
Yeah, well so's yours!

360
00:21:13.380 --> 00:21:16.280
You two're too old for this tomfoolery.

361
00:21:15.350 --> 00:21:16.720
Knock that off!

362
00:21:16.720 --> 00:21:18.340
<i>Well, well.</i>

363
00:21:18.340 --> 00:21:20.530
<i>I should have known.</i>

364
00:21:20.530 --> 00:21:23.340
<i>I was imagining something beyond my station.</i>

365
00:21:23.850 --> 00:21:28.850
<i>I don't get to have any dramatic tales.</i>

366
00:21:29.450 --> 00:21:31.450
<i>Rein it in, already.</i>

367
00:21:32.600 --> 00:21:33.900
Honjoji-san.

368
00:21:33.900 --> 00:21:35.180
Yes?

369
00:21:35.180 --> 00:21:38.150
I'd like you to be my friend!

370
00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:43.170
I'm going to a workshop
 in a place called Katsushika soon.

371
00:21:43.170 --> 00:21:44.910
That's in Tokyo!

372
00:21:45.300 --> 00:21:47.700
Huh? You're comin' to Tokyo?

373
00:21:47.700 --> 00:21:48.600
Yep!

374
00:21:48.600 --> 00:21:49.560
What?

375
00:21:49.560 --> 00:21:51.250
You're goin' there too, Nao-chan?

376
00:21:51.020 --> 00:21:56.020
Created by ©Yozuki  |  #VisitUs  t.me/Yozukilk

377
00:21:51.900 --> 00:21:53.460
So, Honjoji-san.

378
00:21:53.990 --> 00:21:56.020
Lookin' forward to seein' ya there!

